06:11.250 --> 06:12.292
<i>♪ Hadithi the hero!</i>

06:12.297 --> 06:14.043
<i>♪ It's all about me ♪</i>

06:14.048 --> 06:16.124
(ANIMALS CHEERING)

06:16.129 --> 06:18.965
Thank you so much!

06:18.970 --> 06:22.922
You're the wind
beneath my wings!

06:22.927 --> 06:26.612
But you may just be
my biggest fan after all.

06:26.687 --> 06:27.785
Perhaps.

06:27.790 --> 06:28.777
But don't forget.

06:28.782 --> 06:31.588
You have fans all
over the Pride Lands.

06:31.593 --> 06:34.226
King Simba. Queen Nala.

06:34.231 --> 06:36.643
You honor me with your presence.

06:36.648 --> 06:40.010
We're glad your travels have brought
you back to the Pride Lands, Hadithi.

06:40.015 --> 06:42.799
Yes. Your return
has brought great joy

06:42.804 --> 06:44.269
all over the Savannah.

06:44.274 --> 06:45.437
Mom? Dad?

06:45.442 --> 06:47.299
You've heard of Hadithi?

06:47.304 --> 06:48.347
Oh, yes.

06:48.352 --> 06:51.319
Hadithi is a hero to animals
throughout the Pride Lands.

06:52.804 --> 06:57.510
We all know, Hadithi is a bird
who never thinks of himself.

06:57.515 --> 07:00.073
Especially when
an animal needs help.

07:00.078 --> 07:03.987
When a hero like Hadithi
returns to the Pride Lands,

07:03.992 --> 07:07.659
it is important for us
to mark the occasion.

07:07.664 --> 07:10.237
And this is why we'd like
to honor you at Pride Rock

07:10.242 --> 07:12.190
with a Royal Mud Print ceremony.

07:12.195 --> 07:14.432
A Royal Mud Print ceremony?

07:14.437 --> 07:15.517
For me?

07:15.522 --> 07:18.307
A Royal Mud Print ceremony!

07:18.312 --> 07:21.206
Un-Bunga-lievable!

07:21.211 --> 07:23.409
What's a Royal
Mud Print ceremony?

07:23.414 --> 07:25.799
Hadithi will press
his talons into wet mud!

07:25.804 --> 07:28.963
When it dries, his prints
will be preserved forever

07:28.968 --> 07:31.057
alongside those of other heroes!

07:31.062 --> 07:32.721
I've seen those prints!

07:32.726 --> 07:34.557
But I've never
seen the ceremony.

07:34.562 --> 07:38.487
(LAUGHS) I can't think of
anyone who deserves it more.

07:38.492 --> 07:40.463
And as Guest of Honor,

07:40.468 --> 07:43.503
it is tradition that you
share your great knowledge

07:43.508 --> 07:46.081
with a younger member
of the Pride lands.

07:46.086 --> 07:48.737
Now, who should it be?

07:48.742 --> 07:50.846
Dad, over here.
Him! Him!

07:50.851 --> 07:53.433
Ah, perhaps, young Ono.

07:53.438 --> 07:54.518
Me?

07:54.523 --> 07:58.110
Very well.
If that's your tradition.

07:58.115 --> 08:00.011
Is there anything else you need?

08:00.016 --> 08:02.930
Oh, that's very kind
of you, King Simba.

08:02.935 --> 08:04.918
But, I don't need much.

08:04.923 --> 08:05.949
Very well.

08:05.954 --> 08:09.987
Although, uh,
speaking of tradition,

08:10.187 --> 08:11.156
as guest of honor,

08:11.161 --> 08:15.412
I assume that you'll be building me
the traditional ceremonial nest?

08:15.417 --> 08:17.522
The ceremonial nest?

08:17.527 --> 08:19.164
Hmm. I've never
heard of that.

08:19.169 --> 08:22.100
But we've also never had
a mud print ceremony

08:22.105 --> 08:23.748
for an eagle before.

08:23.753 --> 08:25.170
That's true.

08:25.175 --> 08:27.088
Birds do these things
differently.

08:27.093 --> 08:29.041
The Lion Guard would be honored

08:29.046 --> 08:31.076
to build the traditional
ceremonial nest!

08:31.081 --> 08:32.990
Uh... Wouldn't we?

08:32.995 --> 08:34.232
Uh...

08:34.238 --> 08:35.955
Sure.
Honored.

08:35.960 --> 08:38.317
Then we shall see you at
the clearing by Pride Rock

08:38.322 --> 08:41.422
just before sundown
for the ceremony.

08:42.919 --> 08:46.329
Thank you, Lion Guard,
for your kind offer.

08:46.334 --> 08:49.149
Aw, what's a little
favor among heroes?

08:49.154 --> 08:53.642
I assume you know how to use the
proper leaves for the nest.

08:53.647 --> 08:55.657
The proper leaves?

08:55.662 --> 08:57.564
In keeping with tradition,

08:57.569 --> 08:59.610
the ceremonial nest
should be made of the leaves

08:59.615 --> 09:03.251
from the top of the tallest
tree in the land.

09:03.295 --> 09:04.315
Seriously?

09:04.320 --> 09:07.017
Well, I don't just make up
these traditions.

09:07.022 --> 09:10.361
It makes sense, the fronds
at the top are the softest.

09:10.366 --> 09:11.994
Fit for a hero.

09:11.999 --> 09:14.415
Exactly, Ono.

09:14.420 --> 09:17.017
Maybe you do know
what you're talking about.

09:17.022 --> 09:19.150
Oh, uh, I do?

09:19.155 --> 09:20.455
Of course, you do, Ono.

09:20.460 --> 09:22.868
And while Ono spends
time with Hadithi,

09:22.873 --> 09:24.924
the rest of us can go
get the special leaves.

09:24.929 --> 09:25.986
Right, guys?

09:25.991 --> 09:27.152
Uh.

09:27.157 --> 09:29.112
Maybe?
Sure we can!

09:29.117 --> 09:31.617
Just point me
to the tallest tree.

09:33.842 --> 09:37.042
It sure was nice of you to let
Ono stay with Hadithi.

09:37.047 --> 09:39.294
Shouldn't we be doing
more important things

09:39.299 --> 09:42.001
than fetching leaves
from the tallest tree?

09:42.006 --> 09:44.556
For some eagle
we've never heard of?

09:44.561 --> 09:47.049
(CHUCKLES) But my
Dad's heard of him.

09:47.054 --> 09:48.120
Yeah!

09:48.125 --> 09:50.011
And he's Ono's biggest hero!

09:50.016 --> 09:53.665
Right. So let's go find
that tallest tree.

09:53.670 --> 09:58.466
The higher you fly, the more
they'll look up to you.

09:58.502 --> 10:00.322
ALL: Ah.

10:00.327 --> 10:02.065
That's all well
and good for storks,

10:02.070 --> 10:04.245
but elephants don't fly.

10:04.250 --> 10:07.043
I think what Hadithi
is trying to say is,

10:07.048 --> 10:10.399
we all have challenges that require
us to rise above ourselves.

10:10.460 --> 10:12.277
To become better than we are.

10:12.282 --> 10:14.345
Ah. Thanks, Ono.

10:14.350 --> 10:16.337
Wise words, Hadithi.

10:16.342 --> 10:18.540
Indeed.

10:18.545 --> 10:21.681
KION: Maybe it wasn't such a
good idea to leave Ono behind.

10:21.686 --> 10:22.800
I got this.

10:22.805 --> 10:24.697
<i>Zuka Zama!</i>

10:24.702 --> 10:26.708
(GRUNTING)

10:26.995 --> 10:28.572
Whoo!

10:31.201 --> 10:33.198
A-ha! Whoa!

10:33.203 --> 10:34.634
You guys should come up.

10:34.639 --> 10:37.059
I can see everything from here!

10:37.064 --> 10:39.587
Just get the leaves
and come down!

10:39.592 --> 10:41.958
But it's the tallest tree
in the Pride Lands.

10:41.963 --> 10:44.114
I can see Pride Rock.

10:44.119 --> 10:46.418
I can see Mekundu Cliffs.

10:46.423 --> 10:49.384
I can see the tallest tree
in the Pride Lands.

10:50.204 --> 10:51.492
Uh-oh.

10:51.497 --> 10:54.996
Did he just say he could see the
tallest tree in the Pride Lands?

10:55.001 --> 10:56.895
(GROANS) Yep.

10:56.900 --> 11:00.356
And everyone will
look up to you.

11:00.361 --> 11:01.747
ALL: Ah.

11:01.791 --> 11:03.762
Thank you for coming, everyone.

11:03.767 --> 11:08.233
And don't forget my Royal Mud Print
ceremony tonight at sundown.

11:08.238 --> 11:09.294
ALL: Hadithi.

11:09.299 --> 11:10.435
Hadithi!

11:10.440 --> 11:11.806
Hadithi!

11:11.848 --> 11:14.166
Everyone! Back off!

11:14.171 --> 11:17.523
Give Hadithi the
respect he deserves!

11:18.234 --> 11:20.063
Thank you, Ono.

11:20.068 --> 11:22.648
It seems you're a natural, too.

11:22.653 --> 11:23.998
I am?

11:24.003 --> 11:25.298
Me?

11:25.303 --> 11:30.322
In that case, do you think you
could show me the Hadithi Spin?

11:30.327 --> 11:34.079
Well, I'd rather not muss my
feathers so close to the ceremony.

11:34.084 --> 11:37.648
Why don't you show me, and I'll
tell you if you're doing it right.

11:37.653 --> 11:39.583
Uh, okay!

11:39.588 --> 11:41.313
Great!

11:44.317 --> 11:47.146
Okay. Here goes.

11:47.151 --> 11:49.375
Three mid-air loops
and a corkscrew.

11:49.380 --> 11:51.234
Hadithi!

11:51.239 --> 11:52.742
You watching?

11:52.747 --> 11:55.742
I sure am!
Give it all you got.

11:56.816 --> 11:58.343
One.

11:58.454 --> 11:59.887
Two.

12:00.157 --> 12:02.323
Three!

12:02.942 --> 12:05.648
Oof! Ahem!

12:05.653 --> 12:07.109
I, uh...

12:07.114 --> 12:10.828
I think possibly I forgot
to compensate for the wind.

12:10.833 --> 12:12.515
Well, that's your mistake,

12:12.520 --> 12:15.258
the wind always
compensates for me.

12:15.263 --> 12:17.359
Oh...

12:17.364 --> 12:19.923
Never mind.
Try it again.

12:19.928 --> 12:23.008
You'll see, Hadithi,
this time I'll get it!

12:28.251 --> 12:29.700
Almost there, little B.

12:29.705 --> 12:31.005
Ah!

12:31.786 --> 12:33.024
I got an idea.

12:33.029 --> 12:35.461
How about we put the
ceremonial nest right here?

12:35.466 --> 12:38.429
(CHUCKLES) I want
to sit right up front.

12:38.434 --> 12:40.593
Hey, birds only.

12:40.598 --> 12:42.915
But we're Hadithi fans too!

12:42.920 --> 12:45.961
It's okay. We'll find
another place to sit.

12:47.263 --> 12:49.461
That was very nice
of you, Mtoto.

12:49.466 --> 12:50.968
I don't mind, Beshte.

12:50.973 --> 12:54.270
After all, you're still
my number one hero!

12:54.275 --> 12:55.445
Huh.

12:55.450 --> 12:57.578
Lot of animals
want to see Hadithi.

12:57.583 --> 12:59.344
Huh. I guess.

12:59.349 --> 13:01.063
So, where is he?

13:01.151 --> 13:02.468
One.

13:02.473 --> 13:05.453
Two. Two and a half loops!

13:05.458 --> 13:06.613
Almost there!

13:06.618 --> 13:08.618
What do you think, Hadithi?

13:09.373 --> 13:10.906
Hadithi?

13:11.228 --> 13:13.291
Oh! Uh.

13:13.296 --> 13:15.867
Oh. Looked great, Ono.

13:16.133 --> 13:17.899
You weren't even watching.

13:17.904 --> 13:20.195
I'm sorry, but I have
to look my best!

13:20.200 --> 13:22.297
It wouldn't do for my fans
to have their hero show up

13:22.302 --> 13:24.773
looking like he just came
in from a windstorm!

13:24.778 --> 13:28.805
Although, it might make
me look even more heroic.

13:30.052 --> 13:32.890
One more try!
I bet I can do it!

13:32.895 --> 13:34.279
I doubt that.

13:34.284 --> 13:35.758
Time to go!

13:35.763 --> 13:38.679
What? But you said
I was a natural.

13:38.684 --> 13:41.273
A natural with the crowd.

13:41.278 --> 13:42.476
You give them what they want.

13:42.481 --> 13:44.256
You play them perfectly.

13:44.261 --> 13:45.357
Play them?

13:45.362 --> 13:46.570
What do you mean?

13:46.575 --> 13:49.523
You always tell them exactly
what they want to hear!

13:49.528 --> 13:50.750
I do?

13:50.755 --> 13:52.828
But, I'm just being honest.

13:52.833 --> 13:54.057
Being honest.

13:54.062 --> 13:55.661
Oh, isn't that interesting.

14:00.367 --> 14:02.233
(GASPS)

14:05.148 --> 14:06.211
Hadithi!

14:06.216 --> 14:07.279
Klipspringers in trouble!

14:07.284 --> 14:08.640
On the rocks just below.

14:08.645 --> 14:11.054
Klipspringers are
excellent climbers.

14:11.059 --> 14:13.251
They got up there,
I'm sure they can get down.

14:13.256 --> 14:15.265
I suppose.

14:15.270 --> 14:16.617
I guess you guys will be fine.

14:16.622 --> 14:19.304
(HYENAS LAUGHING)
ONO: (GASPS) Hyenas?

14:19.309 --> 14:21.580
Hadithi!
It's Janja and his clan!

14:21.585 --> 14:23.685
They've got
the klipspringers cornered!

14:24.267 --> 14:26.320
A whole hyena clan?

14:26.325 --> 14:28.468
We can take 'em out
with the Hadithi Spin!

14:28.473 --> 14:31.907
Uh. Oh. Uh, I don't think
you're ready for that, Ono.

14:31.912 --> 14:33.765
And, I wouldn't want
you to get hurt.

14:33.770 --> 14:35.554
Especially
so close to my ceremony.

14:35.559 --> 14:37.303
Speaking of which, come on.

14:37.308 --> 14:38.383
We're going to be late.

14:38.388 --> 14:40.172
But, the hyenas.

14:40.177 --> 14:42.336
Can't keep my fans waiting.

14:42.341 --> 14:45.211
Hadithi? Why're you leaving?

14:45.487 --> 14:47.687
Guess it's up to me.

14:52.895 --> 14:54.530
Look! Here he comes!

14:54.535 --> 14:57.436
(ALL ANIMALS CHEERING)

15:00.247 --> 15:02.202
Welcome, Hadithi.

15:02.207 --> 15:04.379
Thank you, King Simba.

15:04.384 --> 15:05.953
Very soft.

15:06.176 --> 15:07.789
Yes, this will do.

15:08.078 --> 15:09.307
Where's Ono?

15:09.312 --> 15:12.962
He's, uh, still trying to
get the Hadithi Spin right.

15:12.967 --> 15:15.247
I'm sure he'll be along shortly.

15:15.252 --> 15:17.453
SIMBA: Animals
of the Pride Lands,

15:17.458 --> 15:21.198
we are fortunate to have a
great hero among us today.

15:21.203 --> 15:23.375
The legendary Hadithi.

15:23.380 --> 15:25.093
(ANIMALS CHEERING)

15:25.098 --> 15:29.093
As you all know,
Hadithi is a true hero.

15:29.098 --> 15:33.421
A brave bird, who always
answers the call.

15:33.426 --> 15:35.153
When someone needs help,

15:35.158 --> 15:37.317
Hadithi never thinks of himself.

15:37.322 --> 15:40.703
He thinks of others,
no matter what.

15:41.153 --> 15:43.695
(BLEATING)

15:43.700 --> 15:45.812
What's the matter,
klipspringers?

15:45.817 --> 15:47.593
No place to go?

15:47.598 --> 15:49.040
(LAUGHS)

15:49.045 --> 15:50.515
Yeah!

15:50.520 --> 15:51.942
Good one!

15:51.947 --> 15:54.898
(LAUGHS) It's funny
'cause it's true!

15:54.903 --> 15:56.035
ONO: Back off, Janja!

15:56.040 --> 15:57.149
Uh-oh.

15:57.154 --> 15:59.117
The Lion Guard?

16:00.297 --> 16:02.288
(SNICKERS) No.

16:02.293 --> 16:03.945
It's just little Ono.

16:03.950 --> 16:05.970
All by himself.

16:05.975 --> 16:07.273
Ignore him!

16:07.278 --> 16:08.974
You asked for it.

16:08.979 --> 16:11.538
Time for the Hadithi Spin.

16:11.543 --> 16:14.586
The what?
The Hadithi Spin!

16:16.179 --> 16:17.617
One.

16:17.622 --> 16:19.110
Two.

16:19.115 --> 16:20.178
Oof!

16:20.183 --> 16:21.483
(SCREAMS)

16:23.119 --> 16:24.442
(YELPS)

16:24.447 --> 16:26.454
(GROANS) Oh, no!

16:26.707 --> 16:28.774
(STRAINING)

16:29.292 --> 16:30.715
It's no use.

16:30.720 --> 16:32.199
I'm stuck.

16:32.204 --> 16:34.403
(CHUCKLES) Ooh, Janja!

16:34.408 --> 16:36.739
You hear that?
(LAUGHS)

16:36.744 --> 16:41.266
Sounds like we're gonna have
klipspringer with a side of Ono!

16:41.271 --> 16:42.629
You go ahead, boys.

16:42.634 --> 16:45.406
I'll round up the main course.

16:47.195 --> 16:48.561
Oh.

16:50.408 --> 16:54.473
And once Hadithi presses
his talon into the mud,

16:54.478 --> 16:57.364
we can all be reminded
of his bravery.

16:57.369 --> 16:58.512
His strength.

16:58.517 --> 17:00.989
And his selflessness.

17:00.994 --> 17:05.464
The sacrifice a true hero
always makes to help others.

17:05.470 --> 17:10.239
And there are few heroes as
true as the one we have here.

17:10.243 --> 17:11.329
Hadithi!

17:11.334 --> 17:13.669
(ANIMALS CHEERING)

17:14.570 --> 17:15.950
Ready?

17:16.665 --> 17:20.407
Remember, the higher you fly,

17:21.478 --> 17:24.544
the more they'll look up...

17:24.884 --> 17:26.964
Aw, who am I kidding?

17:26.970 --> 17:28.668
You shouldn't look up to me!

17:28.673 --> 17:30.653
I'm no hero!
(ANIMALS GASPING)

17:30.658 --> 17:32.449
But I know a bird who is!

17:32.454 --> 17:33.638
And he's in trouble!

17:33.643 --> 17:34.731
Ono!

17:34.736 --> 17:37.138
Lion Guard, follow me!

17:37.143 --> 17:39.453
Till the Pride Lands ends...

17:39.458 --> 17:42.044
LION GUARD: Lion Guard defend!

17:42.399 --> 17:45.153
(STRAINING) Come on.

17:46.436 --> 17:49.759
There's Ono!
BESHTE: (GASPS) He's trapped!

17:49.764 --> 17:52.031
I'm on it.<i> Huwezi!</i>

17:56.494 --> 17:58.176
(GROANS)

17:58.181 --> 18:00.184
(HYENAS LAUGHING)

18:01.574 --> 18:03.340
(GRUNTING)

18:06.009 --> 18:08.332
I'd back off if I were you.

18:08.337 --> 18:09.559
(LAUGHS)

18:09.564 --> 18:11.189
What for?

18:11.194 --> 18:13.253
We know you're all alone, Ono.

18:13.258 --> 18:15.584
I wouldn't be so sure
about that!

18:16.976 --> 18:18.658
Uh... Uh-oh.

18:18.663 --> 18:21.280
I don't think he's
all alone no more.

18:21.285 --> 18:24.096
(SNARLS) You got that right.

18:24.161 --> 18:26.658
Run!

18:27.277 --> 18:28.916
Let's get you out
from under there.

18:28.921 --> 18:30.533
Don't worry about me, Fuli.

18:30.538 --> 18:32.243
Go help the klipspringers!

18:32.248 --> 18:34.104
You got it.

18:35.106 --> 18:36.589
Amazing.

18:36.594 --> 18:40.471
Even when you're trapped, you're
still more concerned about others.

18:40.617 --> 18:42.447
I think I could learn from you.

18:42.452 --> 18:44.471
You're a true hero, Ono.

18:44.476 --> 18:45.972
Thank you, Hadithi.

18:45.977 --> 18:48.029
Sorry I left you behind, Ono.

18:48.034 --> 18:50.799
Well, I'm sure
you had a good reason.

18:50.804 --> 18:53.651
Ono, it's time you
knew the truth.

18:53.656 --> 18:54.807
The truth?

18:54.812 --> 18:57.377
None of the stories
about me are true.

18:57.382 --> 18:59.018
That day at Misty Falls?

18:59.023 --> 19:00.589
I fell out of the sky.

19:00.594 --> 19:03.128
There's no Hadithi Spin.

19:03.335 --> 19:04.966
There never was.

19:04.971 --> 19:07.278
Yeah. I kind of
figured that out.

19:07.283 --> 19:10.144
Right about the time I crashed
trying to do the Hadithi Spin.

19:10.149 --> 19:11.166
Oh.

19:11.171 --> 19:13.830
But, it doesn't mean
there can't be one now!

19:13.835 --> 19:15.213
Follow me, Hadithi!

19:15.218 --> 19:16.830
Here we go.

19:16.835 --> 19:19.023
(BLEATING)
(GROWLING)

19:19.028 --> 19:20.594
KION: Back away, Janja!

19:21.671 --> 19:23.729
How're you going to
stop me, Kion?

19:23.734 --> 19:26.432
I'm between you
and the klipspringers.

19:26.437 --> 19:30.620
Yeah, but, we're between you
and the way off this cliff.

19:30.625 --> 19:31.572
Right.

19:31.577 --> 19:33.933
So? Why would I want to leave?

19:33.938 --> 19:36.003
There's so much here to eat.

19:36.008 --> 19:37.502
Not for long.

19:37.507 --> 19:38.738
Now, Beshte!

19:38.743 --> 19:41.398
BESHTE: <i> Twende Kiboko!</i>

19:45.616 --> 19:47.995
Go, guys! Go!

19:48.224 --> 19:49.424
Come on, klipspringers!

19:49.429 --> 19:50.776
Follow me!

19:50.781 --> 19:52.729
You can't get away that easy!

19:52.734 --> 19:54.092
(YELLING)

19:54.097 --> 19:55.674
(GRUNTING)

19:55.679 --> 19:56.902
(LAUGHING)

19:56.907 --> 19:57.949
Sorry, Janja!

19:57.954 --> 19:59.497
Cheezi pushed me!

19:59.502 --> 20:02.369
(GROANS) Never mind!
Come on!

20:03.432 --> 20:04.568
KION: Hurry!

20:04.573 --> 20:06.506
Klipspringers! Run!

20:06.511 --> 20:08.609
Fast as you can,
little klippies!

20:09.112 --> 20:10.437
(BLEATS)

20:10.442 --> 20:12.062
Now!
(LAUGHING)

20:16.953 --> 20:18.426
What?

20:18.431 --> 20:19.997
Whoa!

20:21.958 --> 20:23.119
Come on, Hadithi!

20:23.124 --> 20:24.866
This is fun!

20:24.871 --> 20:28.144
(STAMMERS) Wait,
did he say "Hadithi"?

20:28.732 --> 20:31.002
ONO: (WHOOPING) Yeah.

20:31.007 --> 20:32.455
(ONO LAUGHING)

20:32.460 --> 20:33.422
<i>Poa!</i>

20:33.427 --> 20:35.183
Wow! Look at him go!

20:35.188 --> 20:38.735
I don't know who's more
impressive, Ono or Hadithi!

20:38.740 --> 20:39.821
I do!

20:39.826 --> 20:41.172
Go, Ono!

20:41.177 --> 20:43.577
Yeah! Go, Ono!

20:44.972 --> 20:48.285
Yes. Go, Ono.

20:50.453 --> 20:53.318
Whoa. I don't
feel so good!

20:53.323 --> 20:54.417
(LAUGHS NERVOUSLY)

20:54.422 --> 20:58.023
I think I'm gonna lose my lunch!

20:58.028 --> 21:00.371
Fur brain! We all are!

21:00.376 --> 21:02.175
(SCREAMING)

21:05.484 --> 21:09.399
Who was that big guy
with the feathers?

21:09.404 --> 21:10.719
Don't you know nothin'?

21:10.724 --> 21:13.947
That was Hadithi,
the legendary eagle!

21:13.952 --> 21:16.266
We got beat by a legend?

21:16.271 --> 21:18.051
(LAUGHING)

21:18.056 --> 21:20.345
Oh, my gosh.
That's great!

21:20.350 --> 21:22.313
(JANJA GROANS)

21:25.435 --> 21:28.253
I was supposed to pass
my wisdom on to you.

21:28.258 --> 21:29.680
But instead,

21:29.685 --> 21:32.673
you passed some wisdom onto me.

21:32.717 --> 21:34.798
You know why, kid?

21:34.918 --> 21:37.383
'Cause you're a natural.

21:37.388 --> 21:40.098
A natural hero.

21:40.103 --> 21:42.074
(ANIMALS CHEERING)

21:43.274 --> 21:45.347
Way to go, Ono!

21:45.352 --> 21:49.177
Animals of the Pride Lands,
I give you

21:49.182 --> 21:51.464
Ono the Egret,

21:51.469 --> 21:54.376
creator of the Ono Spin.

21:54.381 --> 21:56.848
(ANIMALS CHEERING)

